children.subject: Thank you! Does this mean I should get on the waitlist as soon as possible to have a higher place in the off-chance I don't declare?

I would get on the waitlist. I enrolled in 170 for Fall 2019 during spring 2019 and I was undeclared, while planning to declare over the summer. I got into the class even though I wasn't declared, but I had to put myself on the waitlist and I was there for a few months before capacity expanded and I got in (170 also had fewer seats than it has when class starts, so it will expand). I could be wrong, but I think 170 usually accommodates everyone who wants to enroll, and many people tend to drop in the beginning, so you may even be able to phase 2 or even adj. list it (but phase 1 it to be safe).

You're placed on the waitlist until either a) adjustment period starts in August or b) your application to declare the major is processed. Usually the latter happens first, and you'll be taken off the waitlist and enrolled as soon as that happens
